                        <p>15th century, before 1474, <placeName key="place_1000080">Italian</placeName> (contemporary with manuscript): wood boards with broad shallow bevel; brown leather, blind-tooled with lines, stamps, strapwork, and with dots showing traces of beige colour; 
                           spine lost; traces of a single lost clasp at centre of fore-edge; edges plain; flyleaves are fragments from a Latin glossed manuscript, 14th century?, Italian (badly worn); the bare wood of the inside front cover includes an ink ex libris dated 1474 and an 
